# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variables — copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values
# `.env.local` is gitignored; never commit real keys.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase — get values from: Dashboard → Project Settings → API Keys
# New key format (replaces legacy JWT keys):
#   Publishable key  → starts with  sb_publishable_...  (replaces anon key)
#   Secret key       → starts with  sb_secret_...       (replaces service_role key)
# Legacy JWT keys still work but are no longer recommended.

# Public — safe to expose to the browser. Inlined into the client bundle by
# Next.js because of the NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix. Used by lib/supabase/client.ts.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_your_key_here

# SECRET — server-side only. Bypasses Row Level Security.
# Used by lib/supabase/server.ts → createAdminClient() in API routes / Server
# Actions / cron jobs. Do NOT prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_, do NOT reference from
# any client component or browser-reachable code. Leaking this key gives
# unrestricted database access to anyone who sees it.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=sb_secret_your_key_here

# App
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
